## Fun!
In my free time, I enjoy making stuff. Sometimes this is [pottery](https://www.instagram.com/paw_projects/), [sourdough](https://www.instagram.com/nomnomnom.s/), or knitting/crocheting. I also enjoy being outdoors, listening to [jazz](https://open.spotify.com/playlist/37i9dQZF1DX4wta20PHgwo?si=mkKIGDzISB61q_tBGndEiw), and dancing. Sometimes all at the same time! I used to live [here](https://ludwigschubert.github.io/twotwelve.house/).

During my undergrad in Operations Research at Princeton, I had great fun learning about how real neural networks (brains!) take in the world with [Jonathan Pillow](https://pillowlab.princeton.edu/) and [Uri Hasson](https://www.hassonlab.com/).

In the more distant past, I’ve also solved for optimal seating arrangements at Google, and I spotted ships at bay with hyperspectral sensors at the Naval Research Lab in DC.

